@nkeim I think there should be a way to turn on progress reports (currently INFO-level) separately from details like the number of subnets (proposed DEBUG-level). Do you think we should add another convenience function or simply document how to set a logging level? I lean toward the latter but I'm open to your preference.

@Crispy1975, imo, I'd not include that option.

My reasoning is that, in general, I think the router should handle the most general concerns and the things that applications cannot or should not reasonably be expected to account for themselves-- gzip, SSL termination, anything having to do with proxying the requests / responses (e.g. determining real end user ip). The thing that all of these have in common is that if the router, as a middle-man, doesn't account for them, they don't work (or at the very least aren't easily accomplished by most application frameworks owing to an expectation that the web server handles those concerns). That's not the case with setting an app-specific response header.

If any other maintainer disagrees, I'm happy to hear another perspective on it.

